# Gitignored PER-NODE runtime copies of fe.conf / be.conf. Doris's init_fe.sh
# APPENDS a priority_networks line to each mounted fe.conf on first init (and
# init_be.sh does the same to be.conf); mounting throwaway copies (staged by
# up.sh from the tracked pristine multi-fe/fe.conf + be.conf) keeps those
# appends out of the repo. Per-node so the three FEs never race on one file.
.fe1.conf.runtime
.fe2.conf.runtime
.fe3.conf.runtime
.be.conf.runtime
